<br>
As I believe someone else mentioned, discipline is a big problem for us.  Because of the nature of KCoG, it probably always will be.  We just aren't going to be able to get a cohesive group that raid together regularly, and we almost always have a LOT of people new to that particular type of target (dragon, plane, etc.) on our raids.  Once people get a bit of experience, their guild has often (fortunately not always) gotten big enough to join the rotations on their own.  That's a handicap we're going to have to work around, because I don't see it going away.<br>
<br>
We also have the handicap of not being able to have a set discipline procedure in place.  With a single guild or formal alliance, if someone breaks raid discipline, they can be barred from some number of future raids or even kicked out.  We don't have that option... if we barred everyone who screwed up, we wouldn't have any raid force left, and who would keep track of it anyway?<br>
<br>
Also, getting one full group of 60+ for break-in isn't something I'd ever count on... there are many days when we'd be lucky to find a full group of 55+ in a raid.  <br>
<br>
That being said, I think there have been some very good points made here, and I think we can all learn alot from discussing what we need to do differently next time.  <br>
<br>
