<br>
1) 55+ Break<br>
Get a solid group of 55+ (preferably 60+) people.  You will need the following:<br>
- a tough tank (60+ Warrior, Paladin, or SK for preference)<br>
- good crowd control (60+ 'chanter or Bard)<br>
- a slower (Shaman or 'chanter for preference, as a Bard will most likely be on crowd control)<br>
- a solid healer (Cleric or CH'ing Druid/Shaman)<br>
- someone who can snare mobs in fear without being resisted much<br>
- as much damage as you can pack in to the group after the above requirements are met<br>
<br>
There are 14 mobs that patrol close enough to the break-in camp to agro someone who is 55+<br>
Keep everyone who is under 55 out of the zone until the camp is clear and safe.  Additional 55+ people can be brought in once the first group is at the camp and stabilized.<br>
<br>
<br>
2) Bard Kite<br>
You will need one or two very brave bards who do not tire easily and a group capable of killing fear mobs.<br>
<br>
Send the bard(s) in and have them agro mobs to the south (and north as well if you have more than one bard) and kite them around in a circle.  The bards should NOT damage the creatures, as they will then summon and kill the bard.  Simple KoS agro should be plenty.<br>
<br>
After the bards enter, send in the kill group.  When they get to the camp, begin pulling creatures off the bards one by one (a simple non AE spell, arrow, or thrown object should be fine). As long as the puller is farther from the group of creatures than the bard kiting them, theoretically, only the tagged critter should agro on the puller.  Kill the creatures in the camp until there are none left.<br>
<br>
The patrol routes that can agro the camp tend to come from the north and south, so if there are bards circling there they should agro the bards first, and not bother the group in camp.<br>
<br>
<br>
